Subject: [PATCH 0/3] platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: add MS-16V5 (GS66 12Ux) support

Adds MSI MS-16V5 (Stealth GS66 12UHS and siblings) support to the in-review
msi-wmi-platform fan-curve/platform_profile/charge series, plus two general
improvements found while enabling it.

Tested on a GS66 12UHS (EC 16V5EMS1.108): hwmon fan RPM + pwm1/pwm2 fan curves
(CPU/GPU), platform_profile (EC shift-mode 0xD2) and battery charge threshold
(EC 0xD7) all work.

Patch 1 adds the board quirk. Patch 2 restores state on firmware resume:
verified by full-EC diff that deep S3/hibernate resets shift-mode, fan mode and
the fan curve tables (s2idle keeps them), so the driver snapshots fan state on
suspend and re-applies profile + fan curve/mode on pm_resume_via_firmware()
(no-op on s2idle). Patch 3 lets a board family be matched by its 4-char EC
firmware ID instead of enumerating every DMI board name.

Note: based on the in-review fan-curve/profile/tdp/battery series and needs
rebasing onto its current revision before submission; TDP (PLx) left unset for
MS-16V5 pending validated limits.

Developed with AI assistance per Documentation/process/coding-assistants.rst
(see Assisted-by trailers); the submitter has reviewed and takes responsibility
per the Signed-off-by.


